{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868241571,"sessionID":"ses_28603395bffe4wgE81er19jlj1","part":{"id":"prt_d79fcce40001DxRMRTFGhPu35o","messageID":"msg_d79fcc790001N0fJ1oz7Jkfe0H","sessionID":"ses_28603395bffe4wgE81er19jlj1","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_797ef1dc08d345468f5c3df0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark to understand:\n1. The overall project structure and directory layout\n2. Any existing sdk-python module or SDK-related code\n3. Any existing tasks.md or task tracking files\n4. Any design documents related to ST-3 or AR-029\n5. How HTTP clients are currently used in the project (if any)\n6. Any existing patterns for SDK development\n\nSearch thoroughly for:\n- Files matching *task* or *TASK* patterns\n- Files matching *ar-029* or *AR-029* patterns\n- Files matching *st-3* or *ST-3* patterns\n- Any sdk-python directory or similar\n- Any HTTP client implementations\n- Any design documents\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of what you find, including file paths and relevant code snippets.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_286031f35ffewPyzCeEttcCk2c (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is my complete summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Exploration Summary\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure and Directory Layout\n\nThe project at `/home/dsj/benchmark` is an **SDD Token Efficiency Evaluation (SDD-TEE) framework**, version 5.1. It is NOT the agentcube project itself -- rather, it is a **benchmark harness** that evaluates AI coding assistants' token efficiency when developing the agentcube project (from `https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube`) using Specification-Driven Development (SDD).\n\n**Top-level directory structure:**\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/\n├── Makefile                    # Unified entry point (all operations via make)\n├── README.md                   # Project documentation\n├── PLAN.md                     # AR-023 through AR-033 implementation plan (1441 lines)\n├── PROPOSAL.md                 # Evaluation framework design document (189 lines)\n├── proposal.md                 # AR-008 Sandbox GC design (421 lines)\n├── task.md                     # Current task description (16 lines, Chinese)\n├── requirements.txt            # Python dependencies\n├── configs/\n│   ├── config.yaml\n│   └── litellm_config.yaml     # LiteLLM Proxy routing config\n├── specs/                      # 43 AR specification files\n│   ├── python-sdk/\n│   │   ├── spec.md             # SDK specification (133 lines)\n│   │   └── design.md           # SDK design (314 lines)\n│   ├── ci-cd/, cli-toolkit/, code-execution/, deployment/\n│   ├── idle-cleanup/, integrations/, sandbox-orchestration/\n│   ├── session-routing/, session-store/\n│   ├── project.md, test_spec.md, testing/\n├── docs/\n│   └── SDD开发Token消耗度量指标体系设计方案.md\n├── scripts/\n│   ├── engine.py               # Main benchmark driver (v5.1, 799 lines)\n│   ├── auditor.py              # LiteLLM JSONL token auditor\n│   ├── schema.py               # Data schema validation\n│   ├── report.py               # HTML report generation\n│   ├── compare.py              # Cross-run comparison\n│   ├── export.py               # CSV/JSON/Markdown export\n│   ├── preflight.py            # Environment validation\n│   ├── equivalence.py          # Code equivalence checking\n│   ├── validate.py, aggregate.py\n│   ├── run_benchmark.sh, batch_benchmark.sh\n│   └── adapters/\n│       ├── base.py             # StageRecord + BaseAdapter\n│       ├── claude_code.py\n│       ├── gemini_cli.py\n│       ├── cursor_cli.py\n│       └── opencode_cli.py\n├── workspaces/v5.1/            # Per-run isolated code workspaces\n└── results/\n    ├── runs/v5.1/              # _full.json + log backups\n    └── reports/v5.1/           # HTML reports\n```\n\n### 2. SDK-Python Module and SDK-Related Code\n\n**There is NO actual `sdk-python/` directory in this repository.** The SDK code exists only as **specifications and design documents** that describe what should be built. The SDK is part of the agentcube target project being developed through the benchmark.\n\n**Key SDK specification files:**\n\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/python-sdk/spec.md` -- The formal SDK specification with Given/When/Then requirements\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/python-sdk/design.md` -- The SDK design document (314 lines)\n\n**The SDK architecture is a 3-layer design:**\n\n```\nPublic Client Layer:        CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\nData Plane Clients:         CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\nControl Plane Client:       ControlPlaneClient\nHTTP Utilities:             create_session, read_token_from_file, get_logger\n```\n\n**Planned SDK package structure** (from `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/python-sdk/design.md`):\n```\nsdk-python/\n├── pyproject.toml                          # Package: agentcube-sdk\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                         # Exports: CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\n│   ├── code_interpreter.py                 # High-level CodeInterpreterClient\n│   ├── agent_runtime.py                    # High-level AgentRuntimeClient\n│   ├── exceptions.py                       # AgentCubeError, CommandExecutionError, SessionError, DataPlaneError\n│   ├── clients/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                     # Re-exports internal clients\n│   │   ├── control_plane.py                # ControlPlaneClient (Workload Manager HTTP)\n│   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (Router HTTP)\n│   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (Router HTTP)\n│   └── utils/\n│       ├── __init__.py                     # Empty module marker\n│       ├── http.py                         # create_session()\n│       ├── utils.py                        # read_token_from_file()\n│       └── log.py                          # get_logger()\n```\n\n**Dependencies** (from spec): `requests`, `PyJWT>=2.0.0`, `cryptography`; `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n\n### 3. Task Tracking Files\n\n**Primary task file:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/task.md` -- Current task description (in Chinese). It describes the goal of establishing token cost baselines for SDD development.\n\n**Per-AR task files in the workspace** (generated during benchmark runs):\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md` -- AR-029 task tracking (currently a template with TODOs)\n- Similar `tasks.md` files exist for AR-001 through AR-029 in the `changes/` directory\n\n**Note:** The `tasks.md` for AR-029 is a **stub template** -- it was not filled in during the benchmark run:\n```markdown\n# AR-029 -- SDK HTTP 底层客户端 -- Tasks\n## T-1: <!-- TODO: Task title -->\n- [ ] <!-- TODO: Verification items -->\n```\n\n### 4. Design Documents Related to ST-3 and AR-029\n\n**AR-029 is specifically about \"SDK HTTP 底层客户端\" (SDK HTTP Underlying Client Layer).**\n\n**Key AR-029 documents:**\n\n1. **Proposal:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-029/proposal.md` (102 lines)\n   - Purpose: Foundational HTTP client infrastructure for the AgentCube Python SDK\n   - Covers: `create_session()`, `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, timeout defaults, exception hierarchy\n\n2. **Design (workspace-generated):** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md` (792 lines)\n   - Comprehensive design covering architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing strategy, and usage examples\n\n3. **Design (spec reference):** `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/python-sdk/design.md` (314 lines)\n   - The reference design from the original agentcube source\n\n4. **Design (stub):** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-029/design.md` (41 lines)\n   - A template with TODO sections (not filled in)\n\n5. **ST-3 Log:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z_logs/AR-029_ST-3.log`\n   - Records the ST-3 (Design Incremental Design) stage execution for AR-029\n   - Shows 5 step_finish events with token counts (total tokens ranging from 15,527 to 44,549)\n   - The model successfully wrote a comprehensive design.md during this stage\n\n**ST-3 (Design Incremental Design)** is stage 3 in the 8-stage SDD workflow:\n| Stage | Name | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| ST-0 | AR Input | Read AR description, build context |\n| ST-1 | Requirements Clarification | Model understands requirements |\n| ST-2 | Spec Incremental Design | Generate/modify OpenSpec files |\n| **ST-3** | **Design Incremental Design** | **Generate/modify design documents** |\n| ST-4 | Task Breakdown | Decompose design into tasks |\n| ST-5 | Development Implementation | Actual code writing |\n| ST-6 | Consistency Verification | Verify implementation vs spec |\n| ST-7 | Merge and Archive | Merge changes to main branch |\n\n### 5. HTTP Client Usage in the Project\n\n**In the benchmark framework itself (scripts/):**\n- The benchmark scripts do NOT use HTTP clients for their core logic. They use `subprocess.run()` to invoke CLI tools.\n- The only HTTP usage is in `preflight.py` (line 274-275) which uses `urllib.request.urlopen()` to check LiteLLM Proxy health:\n```python\nimport urllib.request\nresp = urllib.request.urlopen(f\"http://localhost:{port}/health\", timeout=3)\n```\n\n**In the SDK design (what SHOULD be built):**\nThe SDK uses `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` for connection pooling. Key patterns:\n\n```python\n# From specs/python-sdk/design.md -- create_session utility\ndef create_session(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10) -> requests.Session:\n    session = requests.Session()\n    adapter = requests.adapters.HTTPAdapter(\n        pool_connections=pool_connections,\n        pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize,\n    )\n    session.mount(\"http://\", adapter)\n    session.mount(\"https://\", adapter)\n    return session\n```\n\n**HTTP endpoint contracts:**\n\n| Client | Method | Endpoint | Body |\n|--------|--------|----------|------|\n| ControlPlaneClient | POST | `{base}/v1/code-interpreter` | `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` |\n| ControlPlaneClient | DELETE | `{base}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}` | -- |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlane | POST | `api/execute` | `{\"command\":[...], \"timeout\":\"<n>s\"}` |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlane | POST | `api/files` | JSON with base64 content |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlane | POST | `api/files` (multipart) | File upload |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlane | GET | `api/files/{path}` | Download (stream) |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlane | GET | `api/files?path=...` | List files |\n| AgentRuntimeDataPlane | GET | `{base}/invocations/` | Bootstrap session |\n| AgentRuntimeDataPlane | POST | `{base}/invocations/` | JSON payload |\n\n### 6. Existing Patterns for SDK Development\n\n**From the PLAN.md** (`/home/dsj/benchmark/PLAN.md`, 1441 lines), the SDK development follows these patterns:\n\n**A. Layered Architecture Pattern:**\n```\nHigh-Level Facades (CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient)\n    |\n    v\nData Plane Clients (CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient)\nControl Plane Client (ControlPlaneClient)\n    |\n    v\nHTTP Utilities (create_session, read_token_from_file, get_logger)\n```\n\n**B. Context Manager Pattern:**\nAll clients support `with` statement for proper resource cleanup:\n```python\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=\"http://router:8080\") as client:\n    result = client.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\n```\n\n**C. Distributed Configuration Pattern (no single Config class):**\nEach client resolves its own configuration from arguments or environment variables.\n\n**D. Exception Hierarchy:**\n```\nException\n└── AgentCubeError\n    ├── CommandExecutionError (exit_code, stderr, command)\n    ├── SessionError\n    └── DataPlaneError\n```\n\n**E. Timeout Strategy:**\n- Default: connect=5.0s, read=120s\n- `execute_command` adds +2.0s buffer to read timeout\n- Timeout tuple format: `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)`\n\n**F. Session Header Convention:**\n- All Router requests use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n**G. Adapter Pattern (in the benchmark framework):**\nThe CLI adapters follow a base class pattern:\n```python\n# From scripts/adapters/base.py\nclass BaseAdapter(ABC):\n    @abstractmethod\n    def build_command(self, prompt, workspace) -> list[str]: ...\n    @abstractmethod\n    def parse_native_output(self, log_text) -> StageRecord: ...\n    def run(self, prompt, workspace, log_path, ...) -> StageRecord: ...\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key File Paths Summary\n\n| Category | File Path |\n|----------|-----------|\n| Task file | `/home/dsj/benchmark/task.md` |\n| AR-029 ST-3 log | `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z_logs/AR-029_ST-3.log` |\n| AR-029 proposal | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-029/proposal.md` |\n| AR-029 design (workspace) | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md` |\n| AR-029 tasks (stub) | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md` |\n| SDK spec | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/python-sdk/spec.md` |\n| SDK design | `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/python-sdk/design.md` |\n| Implementation plan | `/home/dsj/benchmark/PLAN.md` |\n| Benchmark engine | `/home/dsj/benchmark/scripts/engine.py` |\n| Adapter base class | `/home/dsj/benchmark/scripts/adapters/base.py` |\n| OpenCode CLI adapter | `/home/dsj/benchmark/scripts/adapters/opencode_cli.py` |\n| Token auditor | `/home/dsj/benchmark/scripts/auditor.py` |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_286031f35ffewPyzCeEttcCk2c","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775868108999,"end":1775868241568}}}}
