{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868312264,"sessionID":"ses_28603395bffe4wgE81er19jlj1","part":{"id":"prt_d79ff0df1001yG4K0BSNmdTDmn","messageID":"msg_d79fefcb0001x83AIqggHtuI5g","sessionID":"ses_28603395bffe4wgE81er19jlj1","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_2a3f0a5ba2234db7b2bfddfb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** sdk-python\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-029/proposal.md`, `design.md`, `specs/python-sdk/spec.md`, `specs/python-sdk/design.md`\n> **Dependency:** None (foundational layer)\n\n---\n\n## T-1: Project scaffolding and package structure\n\n- [ ] Create `sdk-python/` root directory\n- [ ] Create `pyproject.toml` with package metadata (`agentcube-sdk`), dependencies (`requests`, `PyJWT>=2.0.0`, `cryptography`), `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`, and setuptools build config\n- [ ] Create package directories: `agentcube/`, `agentcube/clients/`, `agentcube/utils/`, `tests/`, `examples/`\n- [ ] Create `__init__.py` files for `agentcube/`, `agentcube/clients/`, `agentcube/utils/`\n- [ ] Verify `pip install -e sdk-python/` succeeds\n\n**Verification:** `cd sdk-python && pip install -e . && python -c \"import agentcube; print('OK')\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-2: Exception hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n\n- [ ] Define `AgentCubeError(Exception)` as base class for all SDK exceptions\n- [ ] Define `CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError)` with attributes: `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command`; message format: `\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"`\n- [ ] Define `SessionError(AgentCubeError)` (reserved, not raised by core clients)\n- [ ] Define `DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError)` (reserved, not raised by core clients)\n- [ ] Write unit tests: `test_command_execution_error_attributes`, `test_exception_hierarchy`, `test_session_error_data_plane_error_defined`\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/test_exceptions.py -v`\n\n---\n\n## T-3: HTTP utilities (`agentcube/utils/`)\n\n- [ ] Implement `create_session(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)` in `agentcube/utils/http.py` — returns `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` mounted for `http://` and `https://`\n- [ ] Implement `read_token_from_file(file_path)` in `agentcube/utils/utils.py` — reads and strips token, returns `''` on `FileNotFoundError`\n- [ ] Implement `get_logger(name, level=logging.INFO)` in `agentcube/utils/log.py` — returns configured `logging.Logger`\n- [ ] Export utilities in respective `__init__.py` files\n- [ ] Write unit tests for all three utilities (mock file not found for `read_token_from_file`)\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/test_utils.py -v`\n\n---\n\n## T-4: ControlPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n\n- [ ] Implement `ControlPlaneClient.__init__` with params: `workload_manager_url`, `auth_token`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n- [ ] Implement config resolution: `base_url` ← arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env; `auth_token` ← arg or SA token file (`/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`)\n- [ ] Implement `create_session(name, namespace, metadata, ttl=3600)` — POST `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter`, return `sessionId`, raise `ValueError` if absent\n- [ ] Implement `delete_session(session_id)` — DELETE `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}`, return `True` on 2xx/404, `False` on other failures\n- [ ] Implement `close()` — close underlying `requests.Session`\n- [ ] Implement context manager support (`__enter__`, `__exit__`)\n- [ ] Set headers: `Content-Type: application/json`, `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token non-empty)\n- [ ] Write unit tests: `test_create_session_returns_session_id`, `test_create_session_missing_session_id_raises`, `test_delete_session_404_returns_true`, `test_delete_session_failure_returns_false`, `test_auth_token_from_sa_file`, `test_base_url_from_env`, `test_context_manager_cleanup`\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py -v`\n\n---\n\n## T-5: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n\n- [ ] Implement `__init__` with params: `session_id`, `router_url`, `namespace`, `cr_name`, `base_url`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n- [ ] Implement base URL resolution: if `base_url` is None, construct via `urljoin(router_url, f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n- [ ] Set default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n- [ ] Implement `_request(method, endpoint, body=None, **kwargs)` — internal helper, sets `Content-Type: application/json` when body is set\n- [ ] Implement `execute_command(command, timeout=None)` — POST `api/execute` with JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}`, read timeout = `effective_timeout + 2.0`, raise `CommandExecutionError` on non-zero exit\n- [ ] Implement `run_code(language, code, timeout=None)` — for Python variants, write timestamped `.py` file via `write_file`, then execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n- [ ] Implement `write_file(content, remote_path)` — POST `api/files` with JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n- [ ] Implement `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` — POST `api/files` with multipart form, set `x-agentcube-session-id` header explicitly\n- [ ] Implement `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` — GET `api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True`, write to local file\n- [ ] Implement `list_files(path=\".\")` — GET `api/files` with query `path`\n- [ ] Implement `close()` and context manager support\n- [ ] Write unit tests: `test_execute_command_timeout_buffer`, `test_write_file_base64`, `test_upload_file_multipart_session_header`, `test_download_file_streaming`, `test_list_files_query_parameter`, `test_run_code_python_writes_file`, `test_execute_command_nonzero_exit`\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/test_data_plane.py -v -k \"CodeInterpreter\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-6: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n\n- [ ] Implement `__init__` with params: `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n- [ ] Define class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n- [ ] Implement base URL construction: `urljoin(router_url, f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n- [ ] Implement `bootstrap_session_id()` — GET `base_url`, read `x-agentcube-session-id` response header, raise `ValueError` if missing\n- [ ] Implement `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout=None)` — POST JSON payload with session header, timeout tuple `(connect_timeout, effective_timeout)`\n- [ ] Implement `close()` and context manager support\n- [ ] Write unit tests: `test_bootstrap_session_id`, `test_bootstrap_missing_header_raises`, `test_invoke_with_session_header`, `test_invoke_timeout_tuple`\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/test_data_plane.py -v -k \"AgentRuntime\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-7: CodeInterpreterClient high-level facade (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n\n- [ ] Implement `__init__` with params: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `auth_token`, `verbose`, `session_id`\n- [ ] Implement `router_url` resolution: arg or `ROUTER_URL` env, raise `ValueError` if missing\n- [ ] Implement lifecycle: if `session_id` provided, skip control plane; else call `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` then `_init_data_plane()`\n- [ ] Implement `_init_data_plane()` — create `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, on failure: log warning, `delete_session()`, set `session_id=None`, re-raise\n- [ ] Implement context manager (`__enter__`, `__exit__`) with cleanup via `stop()`\n- [ ] Implement `stop()` — delete session via control plane, close data plane client\n- [ ] Delegate methods: `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files` to `dp_client`\n- [ ] Write unit tests: `test_context_manager_cleanup`, `test_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup`, `test_router_url_required`, `test_reuse_session_id_skips_control_plane`\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py -v`\n\n---\n\n## T-8: AgentRuntimeClient high-level facade (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n\n- [ ] Implement `__init__` with params: `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`\n- [ ] Implement `router_url` resolution: arg or `ROUTER_URL` env\n- [ ] Implement lifecycle: if `session_id` not provided, call `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()`\n- [ ] Implement `invoke(payload, timeout=None)` — require `session_id` to be set, else raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n- [ ] Implement context manager (`__enter__`, `__exit__`) with cleanup via `close()`\n- [ ] Write unit tests: `test_context_manager_cleanup`, `test_bootstrap_session_id`, `test_invoke_without_session`\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/test_agent_runtime.py -v`\n\n---\n\n## T-9: Public package exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`, `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`)\n\n- [ ] Export `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` from `agentcube/__init__.py` with `__all__`\n- [ ] Export `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` from `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` with `__all__`\n- [ ] Verify imports: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient`\n- [ ] Verify internal imports: `from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n\n**Verification:** `python -c \"from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient; from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient; print('OK')\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-10: Usage examples (`examples/`)\n\n- [ ] Create `examples/basic_usage.py` — CodeInterpreterClient context manager demo: execute command, run code, write file, list files\n- [ ] Create `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py` — AgentRuntimeClient context manager demo: invoke with payload, custom timeout override\n- [ ] Verify examples run without import errors (syntax check only, no live services required)\n\n**Verification:** `python -m py_compile examples/basic_usage.py && python -m py_compile examples/agent_runtime_usage.py`\n\n---\n\n## T-11: Full test suite execution and linting\n\n- [ ] Run full test suite: `pytest tests/ -v`\n- [ ] Verify all tests pass (expected: 30+ tests across all modules)\n- [ ] Run linting/type checking if configured (e.g., `ruff check`, `mypy`)\n- [ ] Verify no import errors across all modules\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v --tb=short`\n\n---\n\n## Dependency Graph\n\n```\nT-1 (scaffolding)\n  └── T-2 (exceptions)\n  └── T-3 (utils)\n        └── T-4 (ControlPlaneClient)\n        └── T-5 (CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient)\n        └── T-6 (AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient)\n              └── T-7 (CodeInterpreterClient)\n              └── T-8 (AgentRuntimeClient)\n                    └── T-9 (exports)\n                          └── T-10 (examples)\n                                └── T-11 (full suite)\n```\n\n## Parallelizable Groups\n\n| Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n|-------|-------|---------------|\n| G1 | T-1 | None |\n| G2 | T-2, T-3 | T-1 |\n| G3 | T-4, T-5, T-6 | T-2, T-3 |\n| G4 | T-7, T-8 | T-4, T-5, T-6 |\n| G5 | T-9 | T-7, T-8 |\n| G6 | T-10 | T-9 |\n| G7 | T-11 | T-10 |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| # | Criterion | Command |\n|---|-----------|---------|\n| AC1 | Package installs without errors | `cd sdk-python && pip install -e . && python -c \"import agentcube\"` |\n| AC2 | All exception types defined and inherit from `AgentCubeError` | `pytest tests/test_exceptions.py -v` |\n| AC3 | HTTP utilities work correctly (session pooling, token reading, logging) | `pytest tests/test_utils.py -v` |\n| AC4 | ControlPlaneClient creates/deletes sessions with correct auth and headers | `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py -v` |\n| AC5 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient executes commands, manages files with session header | `pytest tests/test_data_plane.py -v -k \"CodeInterpreter\"` |\n| AC6 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstraps session and invokes with correct headers | `pytest tests/test_data_plane.py -v -k \"AgentRuntime\"` |\n| AC7 | CodeInterpreterClient lifecycle manages session creation/cleanup correctly | `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py -v` |\n| AC8 | AgentRuntimeClient bootstraps session and invokes correctly | `pytest tests/test_agent_runtime.py -v` |\n| AC9 | Public exports work as designed | `python -c \"from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\"` |\n| AC10 | Full test suite passes (30+ tests) | `pytest tests/ -v --tb=short` |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/scripts/auditor.py\">\nERROR [67:21] Type \"None\" is not assignable to declared type \"list[Unknown]\"\n  \"None\" is not assignable to \"list[Unknown]\"\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/scripts/adapters/base.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/scripts/adapters/opencode_cli.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/scripts/engine.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/scripts/auditor.py":[{"range":{"start":{"line":66,"character":20},"end":{"line":66,"character":24}},"message":"Type \"None\" is not assignable to declared type \"list[Unknown]\"\n  \"None\" is not assignable to \"list[Unknown]\"","severity":1,"code":"reportAssignmentType","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportAssignmentType"}}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes